			<div class="commentnumber"><a href="#c66425">61</a></div>
			<span class="authorname">Dan</span> said on March 07, 2011		</div>
		<div class="quote"><p>It's quite easy to do. Just add a link around each image have the links fading back and forth instead of the images. The css would look something like this:</p>
<pre><code>
.fadein a {display:block;}
</pre>
<p></code><br />
And the Javascript would look like this:</p>
<pre><code>$(function(){
    $('.fadein a:gt(0)').hide();
    setInterval(function(){
      $('.fadein a:first-child').fadeOut()
         .next('a').fadeIn()
         .end().appendTo('.fadein');},
      3000);
});</pre>
<p></code>
</p>
</div>
